<TITLE> Benapole shut for 8 hours </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Benapole, Apr 19 (bdnews24.com)  Trade at Benapole land port ground to a halt for about eight hours on Monday following a dispute over bribery. The port staff went back to their work, after meeting twice with the port authorities. The authorities assured them of resolving the dispute soon, the workers said. Nasir Uddin, secretary of the Clearing and Forwarding (C&F) Agent Association of Benapole port, told bdnews24.com that on Sunday, Shahid Udin, in-charge of shed no 9 demanded bribe from a worker, Riazul, when he went to the shed to unload a shipment. When Riazul refused to pay, the two locked into a fist-fight, Nasir said. In retaliation, all the staff stopped work. They also staged demonstrations demanding severe punishment of the officer involved in beating up a worker. Benapole check post (cargo branch) superintendent Ashraf Uddin told bdnews24.com that no goods-laden trucks were able to cross the border from 6am. The agitated workers went back to work at about 2.30pm. bdne
